videos.description: South Carolina's Mikiah Herbert Harrigan hits a step-back jumper and is later called for an unsportsmanlike foul on an elbow to Anriel Howard's face.
videos.headline: Herbert Harrigan called for unsportsmanlike foul on elbow to Howard's face

videos.description: Te'a Cooper tees up a 3-pointer to conclude the first quarter and buries the jumper at the horn for South Carolina.
videos.headline: South Carolina's Cooper buries 3 at buzzer

videos.description: Mississippi State head coach Vic Schaefer gets emotional at halftime when speaking of Chloe Bibby's game-ending injury in the first quarter.
videos.headline: Schaefer chokes up discussing Bibby's game-ending injury

videos.description: Mississippi State's Teaira McCowan swats Te'a Cooper's shot out of bounds for an emphatic block.
videos.headline: McCowan stares down Howard after big block

videos.description: South Carolina's Te'a Cooper is off on her free throw, but gets another look as she banks in a 3 at the third-quarter buzzer.
videos.headline: Cooper calls glass on buzzer-beating 3

videos.description: Brooke Weisbrod speaks with Mississippi State's Teaira McCowan after her stellar outing of 26 points and 24 rebounds vs. South Carolina.
videos.headline: McCowan: Win vs. South Carolina huge for team moving forward

videos.description: Mississippi State's Teaira McCowan tallies 26 points and 24 rebounds in the Bulldogs' 89-74 win vs. No. 15 South Carolina.
